summary: I swear to god, the manufactured outrage against Brie Larson is legitimately one of the most infuriating examples of entitlement...
body:
I swear to god, the manufactured outrage against Brie Larson is legitimately one of the most infuriating examples of entitlement I have ever fucking seen. 

All she did, literally ALL SHE DID, was say that she didn’t want EVERY SINGLE FUCKING PRESS REPRESENTATIVE TO BE A WHITE MAN. Like, what kind of fucking person sees someone say that one demographic shouldn’t COMPLETELY DOMINATE the conversation, and thinks “this is oppressing me”? This should legitimately be the least controversial move possible on an actor’s part. How the fuck does anyone become this fucking upset over that???

summary: I hope Captain Marvel does big numbers because it does seem like Brie Larson has been floundering a bit since Room.
title: I hope Captain Marvel does big numbers because it does seem like Brie Larson has been floundering a bit since Room.
body:
The problem is:

Like, she’s young and attractive and talented and has an Oscar.

But she isn’t your typical sex bomb either. And maybe hasn’t picked the best scripts. 

It seems like Hollywood execs have just been wondering what to do with her.

summary: What was Brie larson like? Why do you think she is fake nice?
question: What was Brie larson like? Why do you think she is fake nice?
answer: Cos I’ve met her few times. She only took photos with fans once I ever saw her. And it was in front of cameras. The first time I ever saw her she walked like a queen ignored fans who waited for hours on the red carpet of HER movie. Didn’t sign or took photos with anyone not even the disabled people and children waiting for her for hours in cold. If freaking Samuel L Jackson can sign so can you.
